<h1>Non-React Component</h1>
<p>For example, Suppose you have some JavaScript that generates a string of HTML:</p>
<pre>
  <%%= server_render_js("(function() { var x = ReactOnRails.getComponent('HelloString').component.world(); console.warn('ran console.warn on the server()'); return x;})()") %>
</pre>
<p>
  That will generate this:
</p>

<hr/>
<pre>
<%= server_render_js("(function() { var x = ReactOnRails.getComponent('HelloString').component.world(); console.warn('ran console.warn on the server()'); return x;})()") %>
</pre>

<hr/>
And be sure to check your console for the server side warn message.<br/>
Note, unlike calling <code>react_component</code>, there's no client side code. It's just server
rendering.
